og="date">August 2000.</date>. Encoding system was created by Elizabeth Perkes in <date era="ce" calendar="gregorian" normal="2007-12" encodinganalog="date">December 2007.</date>.</creation><langusage>Finding aid written in <language encodinganalog="language" langcode="eng" scriptcode="Latn">English</language> in Latin script.</langusage><descrules>Finding aid based on DACS (<title render="italic">Describing Archives: A Content Standard</title>).</descrules></profiledesc><revisiondesc><change><date era="ce" calendar="gregorian" normal="20081203" encodinganalog="date">12/03/2008</date><item>Finding aid reviewed for DACS and Utah Manuscript Association's EAD Best Practice Guidelines by Gina Strack.</item></change><change><date era="ce" calendar="gregorian" normal="20110127" encodinganalog="date">01/27/2011</date><item>Standardized the container list.</item></change></revisiondesc></eadheader><archdesc level="series" type="inventory" relatedencoding="dc"><did><repository><corpname encodinganalog="publisher">Utah State Archives and Records Service </corpname><address><addressline>300 South Rio Grande</addressline><addressline>Salt Lake City, UT 84101-1182</addressline><addressline>801-533-3535</addressline><addressline>historyresearch@utah.gov</addressline></address></repository><unitid encodinganalog="identifier" countrycode="US" repositorycode="US-U-Ar">Series 14182</unitid><origination label="creator" encodinganalog="agency" id="ID_1697"><corpname rules="dacs" encodinganalog="creator" role="creator">District Court (Seventh District : Carbon County)</corpname></origination><unittitle encodinganalog="title">District Court (Seventh District : Carbon County) Civil registers of actions</unittitle><unitdate type="inclusive" era="ce" calendar="gregorian" normal="1850/2013" encodinganalog="date">1896-1987.</unitdate><physdesc><extent encodinganalog="format">13 microfilm reels</extent></physdesc><abstract encodinganalog="description">Registers of action contain notations for documents filed in a civil case.</abstract><physloc encodinganalog="location">These records are housed in the Utah State Archives' permanent storage room.</physloc><langmaterial><language langcode="eng" encodinganalog="language">English</language></langmaterial></did> <scopecontent encodinganalog="description"><p>Civil cases document the legal process and the administration of justice in conjunction with civil proceedings for the determination of a controversy between parties wherein rights are enforced or protected, or wrongs are prevented or redressed. Records and documents pertaining to a particular civil action are filed together by the court clerk and collectively these documents constitute the case file. As these records or actions are filed, the clerk enters them in the registers which comprise this series. The clerk is required as documents enter the case file to make a notation that shows "the nature of each paper filed or writ issued and the substance of each order or judgment of the court and of the returns showing execution of process. The notation of an order or judgment shall show the date the notation is made. When trial by jury has been properly demanded or ordered the clerk shall enter the word "jury" on the page assigned to that action [UCA 79 (b) (2)]."</p><p>A register of actions may contain the following entries for each civil case: name of the attorney for plaintiff and defendant, name of the judge presiding over the case, petitions, complaints, summons, answers to summons, orders from the court, assignment of judges, exhibits, judgment, findings and conclusions, costs, decrees, requests by attorneys for instructions to the jury, verdict, motions for cross complaints or new trials, amendments to previous answers and disclaimers.</p></scopecontent><odd type="researchnote" encodinganalog="description"><head>Research Note</head><p> Researchers should consult this series to ensure finding all the actions which occurred in a case. After July 1, 1987, further logging of actions is done elsewhere in court records.</p></odd><arrangement encodinganalog="description"><p>Numerical by case number, thereunder chronological</p></arrangement> <accessrestrict encodinganalog="rights"><p> This series is classified as Public.</p></accessrestrict><userestrict encodinganalog="rights"><p>These records are available for reproduction and use.</p></userestrict><prefercite><p> Cite the Utah State Archives and Records Service, the creating agency name, the series title, and the series number.</p> </prefercite><acqinfo><p>These records were acquired from the creating agency through established retention schedules.</p></acqinfo><processinfo><p> Registers of Actions were first scheduled in 1983 as permanent records. This series was archivally processed by David Clark in February 2000. After microfilming is completed, the original volumes will be destroyed.</p></processinfo><relatedmaterial encodinganalog="relation"><p>Minute books from the District Court (Seventh District : Carbon County), Series 14180, documents the proceedings of each case.</p><p>Civil case files from the District Court (Seventh District : Carbon County), Series 84954, contains the entire case file listed in these registers.</p></relatedmaterial><controlaccess><controlaccess><subject altrender="nodisplay" source="umabroad">Politics, Government, and Law</subject><subject altrender="nodisplay" source="umanarrow">Civil Procedure and Courts</subject></controlaccess><controlaccess><subject source="lcsh" encodinganalog="subject">Divorce suits--Carbon County (Utah).</subject><subject source="lcsh" encodinganalog="subject">Corporate divestiture--Utah--Carbon County.</subject><subject source="lcsh" encodinganalog="subject">Judgments--Utah--Carbon County.</subject></controlaccess><controlaccess><subject source="lcsh" encodinganalog="subject">Carbon County (Utah)--Trials (Divorce).</subject><subject source="lcsh" encodinganalog="subject">Carbon County (Utah)--Actions and defen